    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Front Warning Lights</title>
        <para>The front warning lights mounted on the upper front cap section are replaceable; the lens can be removed
            to replace burned out bulbs.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Utilizing a step ladder or stand, locate the light to be replaced, or bulb (incandescent
                bulbs) to be changed. With LED lights, the entire light must be replaced.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the lens mounting screws on the light, loosen and remove.</para>
            <figure id="f47003106" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47003106.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003106.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 106. Front Warning Lights (Typical)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WARNING LIGHT LENS MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">WARNING LIGHT LENS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the lens cover and gasket if applicable.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bulb if replacement is necessary.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove light assembly, locate the mounting screws securing light fixture to bus body.
                Loosen and remove mounting screws.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect light connection plug and remove light.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check wire grommet in surface of body prior to installing new light.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow same procedure for other lights that may have to be changed or replaced.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
